Class IOGroupDescriptionParser

java.lang.Object
  com.kuka.roboticsAPI.ioModel.IOGroupDescriptionParser

public final class IOGroupDescriptionParser
extends java.lang.Object

A class to parse a given I/O description file and to generate java code to simplify the access to named I/Os.

This element is an undocumented internal feature. It is not intended to be used by applications as it might change or be removed in future versions.

Method Detail

generateCodeFile

public static java.io.File generateCodeFile(java.io.File ioDescriptionFile,
                                            java.io.File targetFolder,
                                            java.lang.String namespace,
                                            com.kuka.common.properties.SunriseProjectPropertyStore propertyStore)
A static method to parse a given I/O description file and to generate a corresponding Java code file for easy access to the configured I/Os.

Parameters:
ioDescriptionFile - The I/O description file (XML file), which has to be parsed and which is used to generate the Java code file.
targetFolder - Path of the target folder for the generated Java code file.
namespace - The Java namespace / package for the generated Java code file.
propertyStore - the project property store
Returns:
A reference to the automatically generated Java code file.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalStateException - If any error occurs while parsing the I/O description file or while generate the Java code file, a IllegalStateException is thrown.
This element is an undocumented internal feature. It is not intended to be used by applications as it might change or be removed in future versions.

scanForBooleanInputs

public static java.util.List<GroupedIOInformation> scanForBooleanInputs(java.io.File generatedIODescriptionsPath)
Scans for inputs that are boolean. Returns a map with the ioGroup as key and the boolean inputs in an array. If an IOGroup does not contain an boolean input, it is not returned.

Parameters:
generatedIODescriptionsPath - the path where the IOs can be found.
Returns:
A map with the IOGroup name as key and an array of input names as value

scanForBooleanOutputs

public static java.util.List<GroupedIOInformation> scanForBooleanOutputs(java.io.File generatedIODescriptionsPath)
Scans for outputs that are boolean. Returns a map with the ioGroup as key and the boolean outputs in an array. If an IOGroup does not contain an boolean outputs, it is not returned.

Parameters:
generatedIODescriptionsPath - the path where the IOs can be found.
Returns:
A map with the IOGroup name as key and an array of output names as value
